1 capsicum
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 couscous
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet roasted almonds
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
½ packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin
olive oil

• Boil the kettle
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Slice capsicum
• Cook capsicum, tossing, 3-4 mins
• Add beef strips and seasoning and
cook, tossing, until browned, 2 mins
• Season

• In a medium heatproof bowl, place
couscous and stock
• Add boiling water (3/4 cup for 2P /
1 1/2 cups for 4P) and stir
• Immediately cover with a plate and
leave for 5 mins. Fluff up with a fork
and set aside
• Prick a few holes in pumpkin packet.
Microwave until steaming, 2-3 mins
• Roughly chop almonds

• Add pumpkin and mixed leaves to
couscous
• Drizzle with oil, toss and season
• Plate up couscous. Top with beef and
capsicum, dill & parsley mayo and
almonds
• Serve with crumbled cheese (1/2 pkt
for 2P / 1 pkt for 4P)